<TITLE> 3 killed in accident in Savar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, March 3 (bdnews24.com)  Three passengers were killed and 20 others injured when a bus collided with a human hauler in Savar Wednesday morning. The dead are Sanjida Sheikh Sweetie, 20, Beauty Aktar, 22, and Abul Bashar, 30. Sweetie was a worker of the GB Garments at the DEPZ. Identity of other victims were not immediately known. Twenty people were injured in the accident, said police. The accident took place near Bogabari bus stand at Ashulia on the Dhaka-Tangail highway at around 7:30 am, said officer-in-charge of Ashulia Police Station Sirajul Islam. The human hauler was coming from Jamgora to DEPZ. It collided with a bus of Cholonbeel transport, which was coming from the opposite direction, said Islam. The human hauler was smashed in the accident, he said. Police has seized the bus but the driver escaped. bdnew
